<p><b>Limitations.</b> The evaluation is internal on the authors' RealMan setup, and baseline comparisons with π₀.₅ and Being-H0.5 are post-trained on the authors' data and stack. Full reproduction is expensive (128 A800s for ~7 days of pre-training). Tactile feedback is absent, which likely caps contact-rich tasks. The world-model objective is a representation-learning auxiliary loss, not a dynamics model used for planning.</p>

<p><b>Takeaway.</b> EgoSteer is the most complete open-source contribution in this run: data pipeline, robot stack, training code, configs, and checkpoints are all public. The core lesson is that the data-engineering and deployment-engineering gaps for dexterous VLAs can be closed together, and that doing so yields a steerable, generalist dual-hand policy. The scaling and DAgger results are the most robust claims; the baseline comparisons should be read as directional evidence from a home-court setup.</p>

<hr/>

<h1>Agent architectures for long-horizon embodied execution</h1>

<p>Beyond low-level policies, long-horizon embodied agents need a deliberative layer that can plan, delegate, verify, remember, and recover. ABot-AgentOS proposes a full Agent OS stack for this, with the strongest concrete contribution in a typed, source-grounded multi-modal memory graph.</p>

